post_survey.music_making: I studied violin from the ages of 11-18 both in school and through private lessons. I performed with a local chamber quintet for 6 years. I also played with my local community college orchestra (I was not a music or performance major) for two seasons. I am a self-taught acousitc guitarist. I began learning around the age of 14. I was a member of a girl's madrigal choir in high school. In my mid twenties I began singing with several  fold-punk groups and ran a small, but sucessful underground venue. At around 23 I began working at a music store (Guitar Center). I managed that music store for 9 years, during which time I gained a lot of knowledge about music and the industry in general.
post_survey.habit_change: Yes. I tend to listen to music with more complicated instrumentals or sound scapes. When I was younger I paid more attention to lyrics and vocals.
post_survey.habits: none. Thank you. This was really interesting.
